description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Health and Safety Assistants to work with our established H&amp;S Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will help us to provide a service to staff (and sometimes visitors) who wear respiratory protective equipment by conducting fit testing sessions at The Princess Royal Hospital, Telford (PRH) and The Royal Shrewsbury Hospital (RSH). Prior experience is helpful but not essential as we will train you to undertake qualitative and quantitative fit tests in accordance with HSE guidance. Sessions may run during daytimes, evenings and weekends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will undertake administrative duties in support of the Team&#39;s work, and so the successful applicants will need to be IT literate and willing to undertake some office-based duties when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will help us to provide safer working environments by undertaking other practical tasks around Trust sites, and may support H&amp;S Advisors with a range of duties including inspections and visits to Trust workplaces.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have 3 posts available. At least one post will be based at PRH, and one at RSH. We will expect you to work at either site when required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal discussion please contact Kath Titley (H&amp;S Team Manager) or any member of the H&amp;S Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
